\par\pard\plain \tx240\tx720\li720\fi-720\ltrch\loch \ls2\ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Matea\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s \u8220\'93interactionist AI\u8221\'94 - based on player participation rather than GOFAI which thought about technological completeness and interiority.}
\par\pard\plain \tx240\tx720\li720\fi-720\ltrch\loch \ls2\ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Huizinga\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s }{\f3\fs24\b0\i1 \loch\af3\hich\af3\dbch\af3\uc1\u8220\'93playing of the mind\u8221\'94 }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 in personification - let the mind do some of the processing.}
\par\pard\plain \tx240\tx720\li720\fi-720\ltrch\loch \ls2\ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 This is essentially what \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93believability\u8221\'94 is, as an approach - relying on the player\u8217\'92s imagination to }{\f3\fs24\b0\i1 perceive}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  the agents as fully-formed beings. T&B - believability as 'experienced' (in player's mind) rather than 'encoded' (drawing on magerko's work on believability being in the eye of the beholder). }{\f3\fs24\b0\i1 "the field of intentional agents within computer science can be seen as creating programs to which humans take the intentional stance" }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 - NIM looking at this as well. }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Thus, the general idea of believability is to enhance and ease human\endash machine interaction by using natural and intuitive codes of human communication\u8221\'94 -  Humans have certain expectations about communicative signals, patterns, and reactions of interaction partners. Believability of an ECA means that humans can apply their usual mental models of communication.}
\par\pard\plain \tx240\tx720\li720\fi-720\ltrch\loch \ls2\ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93The beauty of the NPC illusion is that, when well-done, it can hide enormous limitations in the interactivity of the character.\u8221\'94}
\par\pard\plain \tx240\tx720\li720\fi-720\ltrch\loch \ls2\ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 User Model and System Model - about the allying the two of them. "mental models are not always accurate" - "Mental Models" (1983 & 2006, Johnson-Laird) paper, "internal model" Veldhuyzen and Stassen (1976) 1953 Kenneth Craik used the term, Willet Kempton's "folk theory", using simulation to inform decisions - princeton paper talks about applying rules in a mental simulation - conditionals, etc - "A mental model is a representation of some domain or situation that supports understanding, reasoning, and prediction" (Gentner) - "naive or folk theories" - "qualitiative relations" between things - Games are very interested in neuroscience and player's perceptions - (The Gamer's Brain, Celia Hodent) - design is all about predicting errors in mental models and allowing for them. }
\par\pard\plain \tx240\tx720\li720\fi-720\ltrch\loch \ls2\ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 In McCorduck\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s definition, I am not creating intelligence, bu inviting it.}
\par\pard\plain \tx240\tx720\li720\fi-720\ltrch\loch \ls2\ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Less narratively - through affordance, \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93juice\u8221\'94, the work of Donald Norman, }
\par\pard\plain \tx240\tx720\li720\fi-720\ltrch\loch \ls2\ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Remember, imagination is a continuum - therefore, in all cases, it is about entering into a reception contract, both subconscious and conscious, to allow what is represented to resonate - and that resonance can be triggered by very small representations.}
\par\pard\plain \tx240\tx720\li720\fi-720\ltrch\loch \ls2\ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93The architecture is crafted in such a way as to enable just those authorial affordances that allow the artists to manipulate the interpretive affordances dictated by the concept of the piece.\u8221\'94 }
