\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 "AI researcher strives to eliminate any reference to human perception of their artifact" - what about HCI, I think he's being reductive.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Believability comes close to what we want - both how the look and the system.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Naive physics of computing\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Semiotics relates to our ability to understand that signs represent. }
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Games are not just mechnical constraints, but semiotic constraints as well - affordances.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Glitches in a character\u8217\'92s though process can be interpreted in many acceptable ways (hestiation, sluggisheness, character flaws)\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Naomi Alderman talking about parsing her character's flaws.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Computer interface acts as a code that carries cultural messages\u8221\'94?}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 "It remains to be seen whether we can capture the illusion of "the incalculability of life" with the emotional calculus of the computer. In the meantime, the most pleasurably surprising interactive characters may be those who are created with considerably less programming."}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Reversal of Weiz' prophesy in a way - we now realise the limitations of computing, certainly in the arts.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Extra Credits (Enriching Lives) - Geth conundrum in Mass Effect 2 - small computational remit, but the narrative remit provides the depth. }
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Don't always need mechanical stats - the autocosmic tendency will cover the drawing of meaning.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Problem of relying on autocosmics - we "iconify" things we see a lot, break it down. }
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}\f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 "the bare mechanics of the game do not determine its semantic freight" - a combination of the two.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 "the rules [should be] onformed by our understanding of human beings themselves - counters that react according to the newly discovered rules of human minds"}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 S+Z - we "participate in [their] representation" (the characters)}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Narrative descriptors - explicit, concrete representations which help reveal the narrative in games. Essentially representations that use autocosmics to lend narrative meaning to the activities.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}\f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 "It does not come as a surprise, however, that despite fierce opposition, particularly in recent cultural history, aesthetic illusion seems to be more alive than ever and continues to influence the development of contemporary (digital) technology for, in particular, commercial representations (resulting, e.g., in the enhanced life-likeness of films on blu-ray 3 D discs with dolby 5.1 surround sound), since immersion appears to cater well to a fundamental human need for imaginary experience."}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93a conceptual model\u8230\'85 doesn\u8217\'92t have to be complete or even accurate, as long as it is useful\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93dictional personality\u8221\'94 - as performance}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Amazingly, when examined closely, memorable characters in IF are really doing much the same things that their more forgettable counterparts are doing -- roaming about the map, reacting to single words, serving as puzzles to be overcome by the right object or objects to overcome the right puzzle. }
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Talk about autocosmics - about how players (p20) think that the Pacman ghosts have better AI than they do.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Simple things that can give the illusion of intelligence\u8221\'94 - simple things are good, but maybe not good enough.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Games have a cultural context - this informs the autocosmics. Your relationship with these characters. Reflect and transform culture through play. Consider games "as a cultural text".}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Psychological design rationale\u8221\'94 - Carroll and Rosson}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Put the user first, keep the user in the center and remember the user at the end.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93From the user\u8217\'92s perspective, the interface is the system\u8221\'94 - is this a problem? How can this be used?}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 HCI book - computer work is all about human perception and autocosmics - focus on how the eye works.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Principles and results from research in psychology have been distilled into guidelines for design\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 HCI is autocosmics - \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93can help us design interactive systems which support the former and compensate for the latter\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Process of information transfer\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Cognitive architectures\u8221\'94 of users - how their imaginations work.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Employ \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93naive psychology\u8221\'94 - predict what the user will be doing at any one time.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Formal system\u8230\'85 mainfest through experiential output\u8221\'94 - autocosmic interpretation}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Montfort - \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93the establishment of systems that have meaning outside their own closed workings\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 emotions in games guide our responses, our choices and our interactions.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93What videogames do so well is not a sudden phenomenon. It is a continuation and convergence of a variety of art practices over hundreds of years.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Character glitches can become character, can become part of how we play the game - but disconnects the narrative from the gameplay, the experience.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Perceived info\u8221\'94 is autocosmics.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93System fully come to life\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Dormant relationships\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The Cognitivist Theory of Affordances in Games is thus a theoretical contribution, which synthesizes several views by presenting three independent manipulable entities that are relevant to the study of games: 1) real affordances, what actions are possible in a game, 2) perceived affordances, what actions players perceive possible in a game, and 3) feedback, perceptual information introduced in the game by its designers to advertise real}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 affordances in the hopes of eliciting accurate perceived affordances.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}\f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\pard\plain \fi720\ltrch\loch \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b1\i0\ul\ulc0 The Second Half Of This Balance - The Computational, The Systemic}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\pard\plain \tx240\tx720\li720\fi-720\ltrch\loch \ls3\ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Must keep the systemic, computational nature of the medium in mind, and strive to use imagination in conjunction with the systemic - this is the medium we have, and it is only becoming more complicated in this regard. We cannot be scared of, or disregard, the grammar of the medium.}{\f3\fs24\b0\i1  \loch\af3\hich\af3\dbch\af3\uc1\u8220\'93The vocabulary of a game\u8217\'92s system can help convey a story through its very structure.\u8221\'94}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93the expressive power of video games flows through their formal qualities\u8221\'94.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 However, the system itself is also important - this is the stuff of the artist, this is the opportunity, the potential, for comp art. Cannot neglect the system as a medium, as a locale of the meaning. Do not take reader-response ideas that there is no inherent meaning in the text - it is instilled by a human being, the author (need more pro-author rhetoric here?) - somewhere between the formalists and the reader-response people. Need formalism, in a way. We have the opportunity to create systems that have inherent meaning, inherent ways of working that mean something, that we can observe and which resonate with us as we augment them imaginatively as well. Need more of a balance. I see this balance lacking in many games at the moment. }
\par\pard\plain \tx240\tx720\li720\fi-720\sa240\sb240\ltrch\loch \ls3\ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93The AI-based artist should avoid architectural elaborations which are not visible to the audience.\u8221\'94 - not sure I agree with him. Visibility is also a relative thing. Eliza Effect - cannot be completely hidden internal structure, or completely open. (NWF).}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Turkle worries that the rules of games (mathematical in nature) are limiting. She thinks that making the rules too clear is a bad idea - freeform play allows identification, simulation, fictive empathy - we can have both, as has been proved.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 "The entertainment industry has long believed that the highest payoffs would come from offering the public media that combine action and imaginative identification.\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 " the game can withhold some of the complexities of the rules from the player. When the player discovers those complexities later, it feels like a story is developing."}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Looking at Formalist and other positions of character arising emergent from system - I am interested in this, but also we are making a system.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Don\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t just simulate very basic things and leave the narrative significance to non-systemics - must combine the two.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Balance between \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93performance and simulation\u8221\'94 of intelligence.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Pinchbeck - "ecological sense" or "ecological validity" - whether things make sense within the system or through "semantic characterisation" - both are important. }
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Bringjord - Need "rich mental structures", a "theory of mind" - too many deficiencies, too much partiality in the wrong place, and it all falls apart. }
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 They think that "simple engineering tricks" are not enough.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 They can be, sometimes, but don't see them as tricks - as how we relate to other people as well.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Tricking "will always fail" }
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Think about how the autocosmic narratives we are telling ourselves fit the reality of the system.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Consider behaviourism "bankrupt"}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Is necessarily partial (Forrester, 1971)}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 There are some very specific systemics in TWA (\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94level design created a bit of camaraderie\u8221\'94, had \u8220\'93interdependency\u8221\'94), but not a lot, not a lot of room for self-expression - not open, still tightly controlled, manipulated.}
\par\pard\plain \tx240\tx720\li720\fi-720\ltrch\loch \ls1\ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Just relying on imagination can lead to \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93thresholds of credulity\u8221\'94, where the system cannot keep up with the imagination. See this generally in the Problems section.This can lead to a \u8220\'93system\u8221\'94 which is superficially \u8216\'91believable\u8217\'92, but which doesn\u8217\'92t bear up to scrutiny, which is inevitably what players will do. }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf4 Imagination and human computation in the marketing process - simulate the game before it exists - this can be a problem. CRIT - Telltale games set an \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8216\'91obvious expectation\u8217\'92 for meaningful choices which is then let down - this is partly marketing - maybe we should talk less mechanistically about this stuff. }
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf4	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf4 "the game can withhold some of the complexities of the rules from the player. When the player discovers those complexities later, it feels like a story is developing."}
\par\pard\plain \fi720\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf4 But they are building a "micromodel" - maybe a full mental model is not possible.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf4 I do have a very simple model of this.}
\par\pard\plain \tx240\tx720\li720\fi-720\ltrch\loch \ls1\ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf4	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf4 Frude -  A much stronger animistic effect can be expected}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf4	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf4 when there is an opportunity for the user to interact with systems that have simulated}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf4	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf4 character.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf4	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf4 Need "animism, artistry and AI" in equal measures. Imagination, authorship and systematics.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf4	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf4 The systematics has been the problem, for Frude.}
\par\pard\plain \tx240\tx720\li720\fi-720\ltrch\loch \ls3\ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Mateas\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92 \u8220\'93interactionist\u8221\'94 approach needs to be balanced with some of the structures from GOFAI. (as I have done in the creature). }
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Not just about authorial intent - must let go to a certain extent, but it certainly seems that bugs are the slipping away of authorial intent from the system - (In Defense of Bethesda\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s Bugs) a player decides that that is the only reality, not what the author \u8216\'91intended\u8217\'92.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Allying the system model and user model does not just mean \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93complete transparency\u8221\'94 - it is about managing not just narrative mystery, but systemic mystery as well, and using each to reveal the other.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}\f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 However, it has been debated whether humanlike internal processes are necessary at all, or whether the replication of surface dis- plays is sufficient for a believable and effective communication. Kra \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u168\'A8mer, Iurgel, and Bente (2005) argue that to reach the ultimate goal of an ECA \endash  to make the human\endash computer interaction more intuitive and to manipulate the emotions of the user \endash  it is not necessary to simulate internal processes in terms of an emotion model or motivation model. Instead they propose a conversational function model where emotional expressions are seen as purely instrumental and disconnected from the feeling of emotions (cf. Fridlund,}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 1991). - don't need to have this, but do need to think about the systems that you do have - are the characters part of this?}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Physical simulation of a person is unnecessary for intelligence\u8221\'94 - comparing to the birth of flight - we are not attempting to fly.}
