\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b1\i0\ul\ulc0\cf1 My Own Attempt At Balance - An Autocosmic Approach}
\par\plain \f1\fs24\b1\i0\ul\ulc0\cf1
\par\pard\plain \tx240\tx720\li720\fi-720\ltrch\loch \ls4\ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The struggles of computational character, if we take Curries\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92/Pearces\u8217\'92 approach, is the struggle of computational narrative itself - how to ally it to the methodology and the form of the computational, not just how to layer a story on top. Separating \u8220\'93game\u8221\'94 and \u8220\'93story\u8221\'94 seems very wrong-headed.}
\par\pard\plain \tx240\tx720\li720\fi-720\ltrch\loch \ls4\ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Computational art\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s interest in human psychology often seems cynical, or more concerned with \u8216\'91tricks\u8217\'92 - compulsion loops, or utilising more traditional techniques from the arts - such as aesthetic illusion. We are not making bookish or filmic characters. }{\f3\fs24\b0\i1 \loch\af3\hich\af3\dbch\af3\uc1\u8220\'93The majority\u8230\'85 of game stories [are] delivered using techniques from other media.\u8221\'94 - \u8220\'93artists have been working to understand it for millennia.\u8221\'94 }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 - Loyall says to draw on characters from across the arts. Not sure it\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s such a good idea! "comparing new media to print, photography or telvision will never tell us the whole story" - new media is just another kind of computer data. How does this influence characters? Maybe we do not to look to the arts, but not to the explicitly \u8216\'91narrative\u8217\'92 forms.T&B are all about using models \u8220\'93distilled from literary fiction, film and theater\u8221\'94, like Loyall.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 So, autocosmic approach - autocosmics, the totality of imagination, relies on there being something to augment - not just a surface representation, to be computed elsewhere, but something inherent within the world (which we might misunderstand, change or interpret differently, but it is still there) - how can we author this, rather than relying on meaning arising from the glitches? Games use autocosmics all the time, but in a way to create very simplistic characters (mainly based on movement) or for other, less character-based things. They then rely on the resonance techniques of books and films to provide the more "advanced" characterisations, layered into the system itself, or clumsily on top. Look more broadly at the autocosmic, b/c it is closer to real life - not books or films, not merely the "simulation run on the mind", but the simulation run on the computer as well - not one, or the other, but both. My character is limited in many ways (list them) but it is an artistic response to this need to focus on a balance of systemic integrity, a coherence truth within the system, and an imaginative augmentation. It compares and contrasts these techniques. It is not a solution to this issue, but a creative response to it.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}\f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Sometimes offloading the }{\f1\fs24\b1\i0 wrong things }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 onto the imagination, and systematising the wrong things as well. Sticking with game structures not always a good idea. This idea of \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8216\'91not hiding anything\u8217\'92 from the player - this is wrong-headed. A system does need to hide things, they do need to work it out - still needs to be a coherence truth. this is the unique promise. PARRY had a }{\f3\fs24\b0\i1 "rudimentary model of an inner life". }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 More distinctive is what Bungie say about their AI.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f1\fs24\b1\i0	\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f1\fs24\b1\i0 Autocosmics, }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 as a concept, can help us get this balance right again between resonance and systemics.. About understanding imagination as how we see and process the entire world, not divided between real and fictional.}
\par\pard\plain \tx240\tx720\li720\fi-720\ltrch\loch \ls3\ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Waiting In The Sky - creating your own associations from random patterns. }
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Henry Jenkins agrees not to rely too heavily on the narrative form, and not too heavily on mechanics. Other forms are very different. Autocosmics seem to represent game narratives most closely, so focus on that.}
\par\pard\plain \tx240\tx720\li720\fi-720\sa240\sb240\ltrch\loch \ls5\ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  Autocosmics is about thinking about narrative, and character, more generally - more contiguous with life. Computational art is more like life - about creating an environment in which narrative can take place. More like our evolutionary roots. The Longest Night - \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93we\u8217\'92re pattern finders! Find some patterns!\u8221\'94 Koster talks about this, who else? S+Z's semotic approach to games - systematising markers to make meaning - interpreted by audience. Drawing on Saussure\u8217\'92s work. Lucas and Licinio\u8217\'92s \u8220\'93sensemaking\u8221\'94. }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Lend themselves really well to interpretation - "partly told without words" - more like a real system, like the real world (Solutions). (Clark) - \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Perceiving stories is part of how we understand our world. Just as we can see patterns in the arrangement of shapes and forms\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 animals in the clouds or a face in the knots of a tree\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 we make stories out of things that happen around us. We impose a pattern, a meaningful sequence, on a set of events, and a story emerges. }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93This, then, is one of the most basic ways in which videogames speak to us as the real world does, directly to the visceral, animal brain\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0  even as they tease the higher imagination by building a universe that could never exist\u8221\'94. Videogames }{\f3\fs24\b0\i1 \loch\af3\hich\af3\dbch\af3\uc1\u8220\'93continuous wiith real life in a way that is instrumental.\u8221\'94 }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 (Keogh) - He calls games the aesthetic form of everyday life - links to autocosmics.Manovich - \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93book and computer interfaces \u8220\'93fundamentally different and ultimately incompatible approaches\u8221\'94}
\par\pard\plain \sa240\sb240\ltrch\loch \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\pard\plain \tx240\tx720\li720\fi-720\ltrch\loch \ls4\ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Gives us leave to look away from the other arts towards those arenas in which imagination in general matters. Broaden our sources of inspiration. Somewhere in between this idea of "story as exertion" and "story as intermission". \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I freely embrace approaches from any ideology or combination of ideologies that allows the best progress toward believable Agents\u8221\'94. McCorduck - poetry is individual view (romantic), science is universal view (pragamtic) - \u8220\'93neither view obviates the other\u8221\'94 - \u8220\'93when you start making things outside of the convention of what is normal or good or "best practices", you're also shedding some of the baggage that comes with the concept of what a game "should" be.\u8221\'94 }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 "it is critical that games be placed in context with the rest of human endeavor so that game designers can feel comfortable venutring outside their field in search of innovative ideas"}
\par\pard\plain \fi720\ltrch\loch \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\pard\plain \tx240\tx720\li720\sa240\sb240\ltrch\loch \ls4\ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Specifically a methodology for authors wishing to say something - an }{\f1\fs24\b1\i0 authored approach (look at the title). }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 -}{\f3\fs24\b0\i1  \loch\af3\hich\af3\dbch\af3\uc1\u8220\'93Players want to have the experience that a worthy game intends\u8221\'94, \u8220\'93focus on player takeaways and outcomes often outweighs consideration for the artists intent\u8221\'94}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  (Dan Solberg). Resonance is not about slavish devotion to what you think your audience wants. Dispense with or at least significantly reframe the author\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s role as creator of content - celia pearce - disagree - still the author, still part of it, need to author it. "know thy user" - the hci mantra (in interaction design book) Hansen 1971 - we are interested in this in a way, but more about creating art for ourselves - this is the thing with resonance - more about the human. "user experience... has become the central concern of interaction design" - "user experience" instead of "illusion". A narrative that is evaluated, like anyuthing else. "one cannot design a user experience, only design for a user experience". Less about the "corect" user experience (as in product design) and more about an "interesting" user experience (as in art). A methodology where \u8220\'93design and code\u8221\'94 (Griesmer) overlap - theory and practicality - specific approaches and general metaphors. Still authored story, traditional elements and assets, not entirely \u8220\'93player-driven\u8221\'94. Aesthetics are still important (David O\u8217\'92Reailly), but away from \u8220\'93surface style\u8221\'94 to how the assets work together as a system of meaning. Also interested in "authorial affordance" - how the system allows for artistic expression by the artist 'under the hood'. The story of it as an object MADE BY SOMEONE is important. Leigh Alexander - bring back linear, written narratives -> writers need to be part of design team. \u8220\'93Participation in an immersive environment has to be carefully structured and constrained.\u8221\'94 They say that the issue of agent dynamism has to come from method learning rather than hand-coded knowledge engineering. \u8220\'93Refusal to author results in\u8230\'85banality\u8221\'94 - Expressing a detailed interactive character\u8217\'92s behavior in Hap is an artistic expression just as painting or animation is. - Loyall}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Agree with Laurel that should work with a representation of internal system, not directly - but how should that representation look?}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The Formalists - interested in the system, the 'text'. Big links in computational narratology.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Currently in art practice don't care about tech/system - "The machine itself is considered a hack, an accidental byproduct of the artist's engagement with the concept of the piece. In the documentation of electronic media works, the internal structure of the machine is almost systematically effaced." - is this still true? Hiding gaps, the simplicity of it, maybe, or deliberately mystifying the machine underneath. Idon't want to do this either}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Expressive AI does sit somewhere in the middle. using interaction to express a system.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 "interaction design than appearance design to foster the social human\endash agent relation\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Kismet by Brazeal - this sort of socially situated, learning robot - a big project - learn from people, draw people in - \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93\u8220\'93Kismet is a social robot designed to socially interact with humans\u8221\'94 - good mix of human and performance, looking outside the box.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Best games are the ones that tightly marry their narrative (if they have one) to play in order to make both meaningful.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Simulations must be reducible to maths - this does present a challenge.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93The meaningful play that you provide for your players emerges from the designed system of a game - and how that game interacts with larger social and cultural systems.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 "the emotional power of video games draws heavily on the computer power with that supports a simulated world and a meditative environment."}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You do get quite attached to them, despite the limited interactions you have with them\u8221\'94.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Literary works, according to this}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 model,resemblemachines: theyaretheresultofaninten-}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 tional human activity in which a specific skill transforms}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 rawmaterialintoacomplexmechanismsuitableforapar-}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ticular purpose\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94 (Steiner, \u8220\'93Russian Formalism\u8221\'94 18)}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Through observation of a complex system, stop iconifying.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 We are fighting against autocosmics, to a certain extent. We over-simplify because of twitch responses of people.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Better graophics, better plots, stories, sound effects, music etc. but not better systems. Not just better systems for char, but better resonance}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Observabilirt\u8221\'94 - but black boxes are also important.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Honesty\u8221\'94 in how a system works - not necessarily, a system keeping its secrets\u8230\'85}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 "cultural layer" (what is represented) and the "computer layer" (the raw data)}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 HCI balances "between the two poles of computer logic and human logic" - perception, cognition, causality and motivation.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext\f0\fs24\b0\i0	\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u9679\'3F	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 NWF - surface between data/processes and audience. Don't want to obscure systems complete (Talespin Effect)}
